<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
    ServiceNow Update Set record-definition for the `sys_dictionary` row that
    declares the `pending_reason` Choice field on the `x_[scope]_case` custom
    table inside the scoped application `x_[scope]`.

    Per AAP Section 0.4.1 (Refactored Structure Planning) and the assigned
    folder description:
        Field            Type      Constraints
        pending_reason   Choice    Awaiting Info, Awaiting Third Party, Other
                                   (optional - relevant only when status=Pending)

    NOTE: `pending_reason` is INTERNAL SUPPORTING SCAFFOLDING - it is NOT one
    of the 12 core user-prompt fields enumerated in AAP Section 0.5.7's
    verbatim data-model table. It exists solely to support the state-machine
    transition `In Progress -> Pending` per AAP Section 0.5.5 verbatim:
        "In Progress -> Pending: None; sets pending_reason
         (Awaiting Info / Awaiting Third Party / Other)"
    The companion transition `Pending -> In Progress` clears this field per
    AAP Section 0.5.5 verbatim:
        "Pending -> In Progress: None; clears pending_reason"

    THIS FIELD IS A CONDITIONAL, NON-MANDATORY ATTRIBUTE. The other five
    statuses (Draft, Open, In Progress, Resolved, Closed) all legitimately
    leave this field empty. The Pending status alone implies a populated
    `pending_reason`. The conditional logic is enforced by the Flow Designer
    sub-flows and Business Rules listed below; the dictionary entry itself
    encodes only the column shape.

    This dictionary entry ONLY declares that the `pending_reason` Choice
    field exists on the parent table. The choice values themselves
    (Awaiting Info, Awaiting Third Party, Other) are authored as separate
    sys_choice records in ../choices/sys_choice_case_pending_reason.xml.
    This separation is a deliberate consequence of the ServiceNow Choice-
    field design pattern: a sys_dictionary row declares the column shape;
    sibling sys_choice rows declare the allowed string-label values keyed
    by `name` + `element` lookup against this entry. New pending reasons
    can later be added by appending sys_choice rows WITHOUT altering this
    dictionary entry, mirroring the AAP-stipulated extensibility for
    pending-status taxonomies that may emerge once the POC scope graduates
    to production use cases.

    Semantic source-side reference (read-only, NOT byte-for-byte ported):
      - acm-plugins/acm-default-plugins/acm-case-file-plugin/src/main/java/
        com/armedia/acm/plugins/casefile/model/CaseFile.java does NOT carry
        a flat `pending_reason` String column on the `acm_case_file` table.
        ArkCase's case-status taxonomy was driven by the `cm_case_status`
        column (lines 141-142) and an associated ChangeCaseStatus history
        entity (../casefile/model/ChangeCaseStatus.java) whose
        IN_APPROVAL / DRAFT / APPROVED enumeration covered approval-flow
        states but did NOT include a discrete "Pending" sub-state with a
        typed reason code. The closest semantic ancestors in the ArkCase
        codebase are:
          * acm-plugins/acm-default-plugins/acm-task-plugin/src/main/java/
            com/armedia/acm/plugins/task/model/AcmTask.java's pendingStatus
            attribute (a String tracking the task's pending sub-state),
            which establishes the broader ArkCase pattern of pairing a
            primary status with a free-form pending-status label.
          * The ../flows/sub_flows/validate_pending_transition.xml flow
            replaces the implicit ArkCase pattern with an explicit, typed
            three-value Choice on the case row itself.
        The ServiceNow target therefore ADDS this field as part of the
        target-side state-machine design, NOT as a port of an existing
        ArkCase field. The constraint to a closed Choice vocabulary
        (rather than a free-form String like AcmTask.pendingStatus) is
        deliberate: it (a) keeps the Manager View dashboard analytics
        deterministic if a future report is added to group by reason,
        (b) prevents typo-driven splitting of the same logical reason
        across multiple labels, (c) lets a future flow (e.g., escalation
        on long-running "Awaiting Third Party" cases) match against a
        stable enumerated value rather than fuzzy-matching free text.

    Constraints honored (AAP Sections 0.7.1, 0.7.2, 0.7.4):
      - Scope-namespace exclusivity: `<name>` resolves to `x_[scope]_case`
        within the scoped application, and `<sys_scope>` / `<sys_package>`
        bind THIS dictionary record to the same scope by `source` attribute
        lookup. NO global-scope writes - the OOB tables `task`, `incident`,
        `sys_user`, etc. are never modified.
      - Zero hardcoded cross-reference sys_ids: the `<sys_scope>` and
        `<sys_package>` text-node values resolve by scope source name
        (`x_[scope]`), not by literal sys_id. The `<sys_id>`
        text-node value is THIS record's own deterministic primary key
        (MD5 of the canonical field identifier
        `x_[scope]_case.pending_reason`) and is NOT a reference to any
        other record. The deterministic derivation makes the Update Set
        re-importable on a fresh PDI without sys_id collisions: re-importing
        the same XML on the same or any future PDI resolves the same sys_id
        and idempotently updates the same dictionary row rather than
        creating a duplicate. This deterministic-sys_id discipline applies
        to every dictionary entry in this Update Set.
      - The literal `[scope]` placeholder is preserved per AAP convention;
        the PDI auto-assigns the actual scope id at App Engine Studio
        creation time.
      - mandatory=false at the dictionary level. This is CRITICAL: forcing
        always-required would break the data model because Draft, Open,
        In Progress, Resolved, and Closed cases all legitimately have an
        empty `pending_reason`. Only the Pending status implies a populated
        value, and that conditionality is enforced not by the dictionary
        but by:
          * ../flows/sub_flows/validate_pending_transition.xml (sets the
            field as part of the In Progress -> Pending transition flow,
            which is the ONLY pathway by which a case can enter Pending),
          * ../business_rules/x_[scope]_clear_pending_reason_on_inprogress
            .xml (clears the field on Pending -> In Progress transition).
        Per AAP Section 0.5.5 the In Progress -> Pending transition has
        no required-condition gate ("None; sets pending_reason"), but the
        flow itself prompts the user for the reason before completing the
        transition; the prompted value is then written to this column.
        The mandatory=false dictionary configuration is what allows the
        column to remain empty for all other statuses without violating
        platform-level validation on insert/update.
      - read_only=false: an internal user (case_manager or assigned
        case_agent under AAP Section 0.5.6 "Assigned only" condition)
        editing a Pending case may correct an erroneous reason or update
        it as new information emerges (e.g., a case initially flagged
        "Awaiting Info" may shift to "Awaiting Third Party" once the
        requester responds but a vendor is now blocking). Setting
        read_only=true here would require a flow re-traversal to update
        the reason, which is unnecessary friction for a categorical
        attribute that does NOT itself drive a state transition.
      - default_value is EMPTY (no implicit default) per the agent prompt
        Phase 4 verbatim. Defaulting silently to "Other" or "Awaiting Info"
        would (a) populate the column for non-Pending cases that should
        legitimately leave it empty, (b) skew any future analytics that
        group by reason, (c) hide genuine "user did not specify" cases
        behind a fabricated catch-all. The flow that transitions to
        Pending status will prompt the user for the reason; until then,
        the field is empty.
      - active=true, display=true: the field appears on the form (so
        case_manager and assigned case_agent can see why a case is
        Pending without having to navigate to the audit log) and is
        evaluated by the platform for validation/display. Per AAP
        Section 0.7.4 it is NOT exposed by the case-status-lookup
        portal endpoint - the lookup returns ONLY status, subject,
        opened_date - so display=true here governs the INTERNAL form,
        not the external portal.
      - audit=false: the field tracks a categorical attribute that
        coexists with the audited `status` field. Per AAP Section 0.7.2
        this POC is scoped to functional capability, not full audit-trail
        compliance. The status field (../dictionary/x_[scope]_case_status
        .xml) IS audited because every state transition must be
        reconstructable for forensic correctness; pending_reason, being
        an attribute of an in-flight Pending state and being cleared on
        the way out, does not require independent audit fidelity for the
        POC scope (the status-change history adequately reconstructs
        when the case was Pending; the reason can be inferred from
        contemporaneous activity).
      - max_length=40: sufficient for "Awaiting Third Party" (19 chars,
        the longest of the three defined labels) plus comfortable
        headroom for future extensible labels (e.g., "Awaiting Legal
        Review", "Awaiting Translation"). The other defined labels are
        "Awaiting Info" (12 chars) and "Other" (5 chars). Aligning to
        the same max_length=40 used by the type, status, and priority
        Choice fields keeps the Choice-field column-shape consistent
        across the table.
      - choice=3 = "Choice list, no description column" - the standard
        Choice-field configuration when a sibling sys_choice record set
        defines the allowed values without a long-form description
        column on the dropdown. This matches the convention used by the
        type, status, and priority Choice fields on the same table.
      - No reference target: this is a String-backed Choice field, not
        a Reference field. All `<reference*>` elements are empty and
        `<table_reference>false</table_reference>`.
      - text_index=false: pending_reason is a low-cardinality enumerated
        Choice (three values), so full-text indexing would be wasteful.
        The platform's standard list/report/dashboard surface filters on
        the column directly via GlideRecord addQuery without needing a
        full-text index.
      - No PII: the field stores only categorical labels chosen from a
        controlled vocabulary; no real names, email addresses, or
        organizational identifiers are derived from or stored in this
        column.

    Cross-references (AAP Section 0.5.2 dependency ordering):
      - This record MUST load AFTER `../tables/x_[scope]_case.xml`
        (parent table), since `<name>x_[scope]_case</name>` references
        the table by name.
      - This record MUST load BEFORE the consumers that read or write
        the `pending_reason` column:
          * ../choices/sys_choice_case_pending_reason.xml (the choice
            values Awaiting Info, Awaiting Third Party, Other - which
            reference this dictionary entry by `name` + `element` lookup)
          * ../flows/sub_flows/validate_pending_transition.xml (sets this
            field as part of the In Progress -> Pending transition; the
            flow prompts the user for one of the three Choice values)
          * ../business_rules/x_[scope]_clear_pending_reason_on_inprogress
            .xml (clears this field when status transitions back from
            Pending to In Progress, ensuring the column remains empty
            for non-Pending statuses)
          * ../seed-data/cases/x_[scope]_case_demo_*.xml (the synthetic
            demo case representing the Pending status - case_demo_04 per
            AAP Section 0.4.1 - populates this field to exercise the
            "field appears on form for Pending cases" UI behavior; the
            other nine demo cases leave this field empty per the
            non-mandatory dictionary configuration)
-->
<record_update table="sys_dictionary">
    <sys_dictionary action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <active>true</active>
        <array>false</array>
        <attributes/>
        <audit>false</audit>
        <calculation/>
        <choice>3</choice>
        <choice_field/>
        <choice_table/>
        <column_label>Pending Reason</column_label>
        <comments>Internal supporting Choice field set by flows/sub_flows/validate_pending_transition.xml when status transitions to Pending; cleared by business_rules/x_[scope]_clear_pending_reason_on_inprogress.xml on Pending-&gt;In Progress. Values: Awaiting Info, Awaiting Third Party, Other.</comments>
        <create_roles/>
        <default_value/>
        <defaultsort/>
        <delete_roles/>
        <dependent/>
        <dependent_on_field/>
        <display>true</display>
        <dynamic_creation>false</dynamic_creation>
        <dynamic_creation_script/>
        <dynamic_default_value/>
        <dynamic_ref_qual/>
        <element>pending_reason</element>
        <element_reference>false</element_reference>
        <foreign_database/>
        <function_definition/>
        <function_field>false</function_field>
        <internal_type>string</internal_type>
        <mandatory>false</mandatory>
        <max_length>40</max_length>
        <name>x_[scope]_case</name>
        <next_element/>
        <primary>false</primary>
        <read_only>false</read_only>
        <read_roles/>
        <reference/>
        <reference_cascade_rule/>
        <reference_floor/>
        <reference_key/>
        <reference_qual/>
